# Boilerplate Integration

## Block Structure

- `blocks/` - Commerce & content blocks
- `scripts/initializers/` - Drop-in initialization
- `scripts/commerce.js` - Commerce utilities

## Block Decoration Pattern

```javascript
export default async function decorate(block) {
  const { render } = await import('@dropins/your-dropin/render.js');
  const Container = (await import('@dropins/your-dropin/containers/YourContainer.js')).default;
  const container = document.createElement('div');
  block.appendChild(container);
  await render.render(Container, { /* props */ })(container);
}
```

## DOM Creation

- **Multiple elements**: `document.createRange().createContextualFragment(\`<div>...</div>\`)`
- **Single element**: `document.createElement('div')`

## Initializers

Drop-ins require providers in `scripts/initializers/`. Use `initializeDropin()` and `initializers.mountImmediately()`.

## Import Maps

Drop-ins loaded via import maps in `head.html`. Add your drop-in under `imports`.
